mportant group member.  Don't let your tank die to save someone who can't absorb damage anyway; you lose your tank you lose your group.  It's all a matter of situation.  In higher levels you'll be wanting to save the wizzie/druid, so they can evac out.  I've been told that in this case, you cast an area effect or group heal (This'll taunt most anything onto you), cast Divine Aura to go invincible, and be ready to click it off a few seconds before the wizzie/druid's port spell is complete.  (If you're invincible, then the port will not take you.  You don't want to be left behind.  =P)<br><br>Anyway, enough rambling from me...<br><br>Jarochai Alabaster<br>28th Dwarven Cleric of Brell Serelis<br>Proud member of Exile<br>Brell Serelis server<br><br>Anyone have any questions, pop into brell and /who me.  If I'm on, I'll try to get in some time to talk if I'm not in a fast group.  =)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
