	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, (takes a DEEP breath), some good some bad being said here.  I'm only a beginning cleric, although I have a high level Shadow Knight and have grouped with many GOOD Clerics.<br><br>First Clerics always melee, the good ones tell the group theyy will be doing it ahead of time, but they all have to melee at every level.  If you don't melee your defense skills fall behind and when you agro a MOB (and you will) at level 40, if your defense is not max YOU WILL DIE.  Even a 45 SK with HT and Desease cloud can't taunt off a MOB once your life drops below half from a couple of solid hits from an enraged MOB.  Use moderation, once your defense skills max for level then you can sit on youe rear through the whole fight, but keep defense MAXED!<br><br>Next, use your full range of spells, a Cleric is not just a healer.  If you have someone that can snare and are fighting outdoors use fear.  Fear Kiting is a tremendus life saver.  If the MOB isn't hitting anyone then you don't need to heal them.  A Cleric fears as well as a Necro or SK, so use it if you can.  <br><br>Stun and Root can also be effective, but Root takes a tremendous amount of mana, use it sparingly, and remember a rooted MOB never turns and stops hitting the tanks, it is sometimes counter productive (especially if its already snared and someone is fearing).<br><br>Smite:  another great spell if used properly, just remember your not a Wizard.<br><br>Healing, bread and butter stuff here.  If people are yelling for a heal your wrong.  But conversly letting a Warrior get below 2 bubbles of health is sometimes a good thing (berzerker furry).  I've seen Tanks request to be kept between 1 and 2 bubbles of life for this reason.  If they trust the Cleric this is a good thing, but until you earn the tanks trust don't try this.  Healing is an art, i never worry about my life when I am grouped with my regular Cleric, I've been below 1/2 a bubble of life and didn't even consider asking for a heal, I knew it was coming.  He also knows when he yells "On Me" I'm GOING to pull the thing off quick, even if I have to HT it.  <br><br>GOOD Clerics are a great asset and don't freelance alot because a GOOD group is hard to find for them too.  Any cleric at lvl 40+ thats looking for a pickup group is immediately suspect to me.  I know our Cleric can't log on more than 10 minutes without us asking him if he needs to get a ride to join us.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
