	   <tr><td colspan=2>We are not obsolete.  We are feeling the pain of those who misused their abilities to the point verant had to make some changes to prevent complete destruction of the game.  I disagree with their changes to clerics, not the motivation.  They needed to make changes, I just think they made the wrong ones.<br><br>As for giving druids and shamen better spells, that was a good idea.  They still don't heal with those spells as well as we do with the same ones.  Now instead of being the only person who can heal in a group, we have a reliable backup healer who can also nuke better than we can when we aren't in a really tight situation and need them medding/healing.  And they can't replace a cleric... not entirely.  In general, you need two druids or shamen to really do the job as well as one cleric.  What would you rather?  A dammage dealer and one healer or two healers unable to help dish out dammage?<br><br>But on the other hand, would you like to be sitting around at the zone unable to kill anything at all waiting for that cleric to finally drop by?  Druids and shamen don't like playing healers, but at least they can now, and that's better than sitting around twiddling your thumbs.<br><br>Now for the heal agro stuff... well that's typical Verant moronicism.  They "fix" most every problem by breaking the game worse and go too far the other direction and then bringing it back some a little bit at a time until they get it "just right"... which usually is actually not quite far enough.  Not the right way to do things.  But it's worked so far when they have no competition.  We'll see if they continue to survive with these methods as the next generation of games begin coming out.<br><br>Cinari Fairiehealer<br>53 cleric<br>Bloodstone Templars<br>Solusek Ro<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
