	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 7th 11:19 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Now that i've reached a level where things are hitting in the high 80's to 100's, i've learned its best to get out of trouble quickly before getting into a bad situation.  One of the best ways to do this is to keep out "godly favor" spell memmed in the top slot at all times.  This spell we get a lvl 1 and uses almost no mana and cast very quickly.  Of course i'm talking about divine aura.  I think most clerics only use this spell at the last possble moment to save themselves from death, much the way a pally would use Lay on Hands.  But i find its better to use it sooner then later because it gets teh mob off you right away, and allows you to step back and med or look at the tanks status and determine when to try to heal again.  Another cool thing about this spell is that even though you can not cast when it is in effect, you can click it off before it runs out and begin casting again or attacking.  I now have this and divine barriar (sp) memmed at all times if possble, and casting them at the first sign of trouble has prevented many a massacres.  Just thought i'd share this advice, do what you want with it.  Geez can i babble on or what:)<br>&nbsp;<br>TeeJ Of Dragon's Claw on Xegony Server<br>TeeJ - 24th Paladin<br>TeeJheal - 52th Cleric - Master Blacksm</td></tr>
