<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98503127856670></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98503127856670><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98503127856670>RE: Lots of Clerics?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98503127856670#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=15781><span id= >Cinari</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 19th 2:47 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Clerics are the most often mis-played class around.  And often we don't get the respect we deserve.  There is a shortage of high level clerics, and even more so a shortage of GOOD clerics on my server.  Partly because it is hard to play a good cleric.  Partly because of some of the recent nerfs.  And there are other factors too.<br><br>As for burnout, it happens all the time with many classes.  I have played almost every class in this game.  My favorite is still a cleric.  Monks are fun, necros can really tear stuff up with their DOTs, warriors can really take a lot of beating, druids can get around better than anybody else tho I find them also a difficult class to play properly, and often misplayed.<br><br>If you are tired of playing a cleric, try another class.  You will either find a cleric is to your taste afterwards and come back, or decide you like the new class better and find your true love.  I actually started as a paladin.  I got tired of how abysmally weak and underpowered they were (this was a looooong time ago tho), started a cleric and have rarely looked back.<br><br>Oh, and Mr "CAMPING OUT", you are right, you are the leader of the group, officially or otherwise. Don't abuse that power.  Or you will need to start learning how to solo really soon.<br><br>Cinari Fairiehealer<br>53 cleric<br>Bloodstone Templars<br>Solusek Ro<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
