<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9840218247224></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9840218247224><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=9840218247224>Nuke/Melee Clerics</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=9840218247224#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35931><span id=Scholar>Shaladarra</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>21 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 7th 10:23 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK this is a bit of a rant.  Recently, I entered a group and there happened to be a 2nd cleric.  To make a long story short, this guy was very nice but he was my nightmaire as far as grouping.  We had agreed that we would each be responsible for healing 2 people.  Within about an hours time here's how it broke down:<br><br>-I noticed that the other cleric's health was dropping so i got up to heal him when to my amazement he was outside of the spell's effect.  Meanwhile we were overrun and due to a lack of tank taunt, I died with 2 bulbs of mana.  The other cleric made it safely to zone (as he had left as soon as all hell broke lose).<br><br>-After I tretrieved my corpse and rejoined the group, I notice to my amazement that the other cleric is up with the tanks meleeing.  It became obvious that he was not healing so I took on an extra group member for healing (giving me 3 and him only 1 of the tanks).  All 3 of mine where healed and I steadily watched his tank drop to 2 bulbs of health.  The tank actually had to ask for him to please heal and not wait unitl after a battle was done.<br><br>Clerics need to realize that a) we are not damage doers, we are just the opposite.  If you want to melee, make a tank.  <br><br>Secondly, a cleric should be the last to gate out of a bad situation.  If you're not prepared to die for the group in order to get that last heal off, then go make a druid or a necro.  You've got no business being in a position where people relyon you to save their life.<br><br>We have Divine Aure and later Divine Barrier.  Use them.  I will be honest in saying when I died I did not have DA memmed (my mistake, I had died the night before thanks to a high level NPC and I didn't mem it.  If I had it at the time, there is a good chance I wouldn't have died since it works as an anti-taunt and has saved my life several times in the past).<br><br>Anyway, there's my 2cp.  Just thought I'd get it off my chest.  I welcome comments.<br>&nbsp;<br>Gabriarra Mistmoon<br>(33 Cleric High Elf)<br>Shaladarra Sowstorm<br>(30 druid wood elf)<br></td></tr>
