	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are many times when a cleric can nuke for the benefit of the group.  Generally a stun is much better than a nuke in most situations, but sometimes nukes are called for.  Two clerics in a group can be one such situation, depends on what you are fighting.  One situation where you should always have a stun ready for is in high level dungeons where you have an evacer (who is also generally a nuker)... he or she may need a few seconds reprieve from getting beat on to evac the group.  Post-50 you may need to stun to keep the chanter from getting summoned while attempting to crowd control.  A lot depends on your particular situation.<br><br>But in your particular case I would say your group member was not firing on all cylinders.<br><br>Melee, I do it, but for one reason and one reason only... a JOKE.  I do it to play with really low greenies.  And every now and then I'll do it to make people laugh at me.  Otherwise, a nuke or a heal are much better uses of your time IMO.<br><br>But I don't want clerics melee skills improved.  We are primarily a defensive class, with some abilities designed to allow us to kill annoying pests that attack us.  We aren't going to take down that angry red (ok green now for me but not you) hill giant solo.  But we can swat the stupid orc pawn that had the temerity to interrupt our meditations.<br><br>To summarize:  In general, a cleric who is full mana should help do some dammage, and a cleric who is not should be medding.  There are exceptions to every rule.  There aren't very many to this one.<br><br>Cinari Fairiehealer<br>53 cleric<br>Bloodstone Templars<br>Solusek Ro<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
