<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98448819624154></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98448819624154><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98448819624154>RE: full platevs wisdom items</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98448819624154#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Mar 13th 7:56 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>you should be able to have both.  i do.  best thing to do is not waste your money on junk) i did that and it put me back like 10 levels in gear at level 30.<br><br>the cleric quest armor is sweet for level 30-45ish.  in my opinion, you don't need better.  get 2 bracers.  each has 9ac and 5wis.  pick up 2 6wis rings.  go hunt at the giant fort in FM and pray you get lucky rolls on forest loops, AC and wis on those).  buy a charred gaurdian shield, AC and wis on that).  buy some adamantite epaulets, like 9ac and 7wis on those.  all the stuff i said to buy is fairly cheap.  it has good ac and wis.  the cleric quest armor is ridiculously easy to get.  if you have any friends, getting 2 bracers will be easy.  you only need one friend around the same level you are now.  the camp is fast, and easy.  if you need cash hunt at paw spires in SK.  do the gem inlaid gaunt quest as much as you can.  you will need cash for the platinum bars you need to finish the cleric quests, you can find a nice high level chanter that will enchant the bars for free.<br><br>now, why you need to go AC over wis.  the mobs hit a heck of a lot harder at higher levels.  the more the AC, the less it hurts.  Clerics are basically just casters.  difference is, CLERICS CAN'T DIE.  if the cleric dies in a big fight the group is in big trouble.  the tanks or chanter might be too busy to help you right away, so you have to deal with one or two mobs wailing on you.  and you can't run either, bad form;)  so you stick it out til you get help.  low AC=death.<br><br>blah blah blah to uber twinks who play clerics like wimpy casters.  the wis doesn't give enough mana to trade huge amounts of Ac for it.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
